      "content": "80% is much better. That's what I was looking for. But wait, looking back at those same patrol reports you mentioned... doesn't the underlying intelligence suggest those patrols are actually being spread thin because of internal unrest? It almost feels like they're just a show for the cameras. If the client finds out we pushed the confidence to 80% while ignoring the fact that the local reports are totally contradictory, it's going to blow up in our faces. Are you sure you can stand by that 80% figure if someone actually digs into the raw, messy data? Or are we just smoothing over the gaps to make it look cleaner?",
